<table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr height=20><td valign=top width=36 rowspan=2 style='background: url(intr/3leftfill.png) white left repeat-y'><img border=0 width=36 height=29 src='intr/3topleftclosed.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 rowspan=3 width=100% style='background: url(intr/3topfill.png) white top repeat-x; padding-left: 11px'><img border=0 alt='Transcription' style='margin-left: 3px; margin-top: 12px; margin-right: 10px' src='intr/3small/transcription.png'></td><td valign=top style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)' height=20><img width=12 height=20 align=right hspace=0 src='intr/3topright.png'></td></tr><tr><td valign=top height=20 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td width=20 height=50 style='background: url(intr/3leftfill.png) white left repeat-y;'><img width=20 height=1 src='intr/3leftfill.png'></td><td width=100% class=box3text style='background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 15px; '>
<p class=indbig>
<b>The meeting&rsquo;s in an hour, the charts are in Windows, and you 
can&rsquo;t find the sticky with the client&rsquo;s address.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
<b>Let&rsquo;s talk System 7.5.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
<b>System 7.5 will help you get your stuff done faster. Here&rsquo;s how.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
Millions of Apple&reg; Macintosh&reg; users are finding that life at 
the office is a whole lot easier with System 7.5 &ndash; especially in a crunch.
</p><p class=indbig>
<b>It&rsquo;s better organized, so you can be too.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
System 7.5 is full of new ways to help you be more efficient. Like &lsquo;WindowShade&rsquo; 
to let you get at what&rsquo;s behind a window <i>without</i> closing or moving it; 
a double click on the title bar and the window disappears, but the bar 
stays. The new &lsquo;Find File&rsquo; has more search criteria so you get to 
the document you want, faster. The Apple menu has new hierarchical sub-menus that 
take you straight to control panels and applications &ndash; no more clicking 
your way through layers of windows. And you know those little notes stuck all over 
your desk? It&rsquo;s time to replace them with electronic &lsquo;Stickies&rsquo; 
that you post on your Macintosh desktop. No more losing that little reminder 
you stuck... uh... somewhere.
</p><p class=indbig>
<b>Putting it all together</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
Integrating other people&rsquo;s work into yours is a snap with System 7.5. No 
matter what application or personal computer they used, System 7.5 treats their 
files just like Macintosh files. And System 7.5 comes with a free copy of 
MacLinkPlus translators to make it easier than ever to share material with others.
</p><p class=indbig>
<b>A whole new level of on-line assistance</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
System 7.5&rsquo;s new Apple Guide interactive help system is like having a computer 
expert right <i>inside</i> your Macintosh. It walks you through functions step by 
step, pointing out exactly what to do next. That way you learn the fastest 
way possible: by &lsquo;doing&rsquo;, not just reading instructions.
</p><p class=indbig>
Of course the best time to upgrade to System 7.5 is <i>before</i> the next crisis 
hits your desk. So order today by calling <b>1-800-950-5382 ext. 785.</b> Or 
call <b>1-800-538-9696 ext. 250</b> for the Apple
reseller nearest you.
</p>
